    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-11-08T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-08T06:00:00-05:00" n="721"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d721">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.51/11–846: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-08T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 8, 1946—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:01 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1174. Prime Minister<note n="46" xml:id="d721fn46">Recep Peker formed a new
                        Turkish Government on August 7.</note> spoke to me yesterday with great
                    earnestness regarding desire obtain additional <gloss target="#t_Eximbank1"
                        >Eximbank</gloss> credit. He said <pb facs="0928" n="916" xml:id="pg_916"/>
                    25,000,000 already granted entirely earmarked essential purposes and number
                    other projects vital to Turkish economy require additional funds, such as
                    communications, transport needs, agricultural and mineral development. He hopes
                    very much we can help and said additional credit at present time would be great
                    material and moral assistance to Turkish Govt and people.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
